HttpsNetworkLocation
public class HttpNetworkLocation extends com.telenav.kivakit.network.core.NetworkLocation implements com.telenav.kivakit.resource.Resourceful
An HTTP network location.

Access

HTTP network locations can be accessed as resources with resource(). The can also be accessed with the HTTP access methods GET, PUT and POST:

  • content(Listener)
  • get() - A HttpGetResource with default content type and access constraints
  • get(String) - A HttpGetResource with the given content type
  • get(NetworkAccessConstraints) - A HttpGetResource with the given access constraints
  • get(NetworkAccessConstraints, String) - A HttpGetResource with the given content type and access constraints
  • post() - A HttpPostResource with default content type and access constraints
  • post(String) - A HttpPostResource with the given content to post
  • post(String, String) - A HttpPostResource with the given content and content to post
  • post(NetworkAccessConstraints) - A HttpPostResource with the given constraints
  • post(NetworkAccessConstraints, String, String) - A HttpPostResource with the given constraints, content type and content to post
  • put(String, String) - A HttpPutResource with the given content type and content to put
  • put(NetworkAccessConstraints, String, String) - A HttpPutResource with the given access constraints, content type and content to put
  • resource()

Functional

  • withInterpolatedVariables(VariableMap)
  • withPath(NetworkPath)
  • withQueryParameters(QueryParameters)
